11/05/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The international community's High Representative to BiH, Paddy Ashdown, urged the young people of Southeast Europe on Monday (10 May) to become active in politics to bring about change in the region. In a speech to the European Youth Peace summit in Sarajevo, Ashdown said the time had come for the youth of the region "to move from the shadows to the front row of politics".
In other news, Republika Srpska's Srebrenica Commission -- investigating events surrounding the July 1995 massacre of Muslims -- is working on its third preliminary report. Earlier efforts were criticised amid claims of government obstruction. (OHR Sources, Oslobodjenje - 11/05/04; Fena - 10/05/04)
